{
  "format": "tiptap/v1",
  "doc": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Anthropic issues rate limits per organization, not per team or service. If four teams each have their own API key with separate limits, you get fragmentation: Team A may hit its limit while Team B's quota sits idle. A custom proxy solves this by exposing a single shared rate-limit pool to all internal callers and enforcing per-team soft caps \u2014 unused capacity from one team flows to others automatically."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Custom proxy rate-limit pooling architecture across teams"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The Problem: Fragmented Rate Limits"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Without pooling, each team requests its own API key and negotiates its own rate limit quota. This creates three problems:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Wasted capacity",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": If Team A uses only 200 of its 500 RPM allocation during off-hours, those 300 RPM are unavailable to other teams \u2014 they hit their own limits even though aggregate capacity exists."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Negotiation overhead",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": Each team separately requests quota increases from Anthropic. Org-level limit increases are simpler to justify with aggregate usage data."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Key sprawl",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": Multiple API keys across teams complicate secret rotation, access control, and cost attribution."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Proxy Design: Token Bucket + Per-Team Quotas"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The proxy enforces two layers of rate limiting: an outer token bucket that matches the org-level Anthropic limit, and per-team soft caps that prevent any one team from monopolizing the pool."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# requirements: fastapi uvicorn httpx redis python-dotenv\nimport asyncio\nimport time\nimport httpx\nfrom fastapi import FastAPI, Request, HTTPException, Header\nfrom fastapi.responses import StreamingResponse\nimport redis.asyncio as redis\n\napp = FastAPI()\n\n# Token bucket state stored in Redis for multi-instance proxy deployments\nredis_client = redis.from_url(\"redis://localhost:6379\")\n\nANTHROPIC_API_KEY = \"sk-ant-...\"   # single real key\nORG_RPM_LIMIT     = 1_000          # your Anthropic org limit\n\n# Soft caps per team (as fraction of org limit)\nTEAM_CAPS = {\n    \"team-a\": 0.40,   # max 40% of pool\n    \"team-b\": 0.30,\n    \"team-c\": 0.20,\n    \"team-d\": 0.10,\n}\nTEAM_KEYS = {\n    \"proxy-key-team-a\": \"team-a\",\n    \"proxy-key-team-b\": \"team-b\",\n    \"proxy-key-team-c\": \"team-c\",\n    \"proxy-key-team-d\": \"team-d\",\n}\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Token Bucket Implementation"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "async def acquire_org_slot(timeout_sec: float = 5.0) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"\n    Try to acquire one RPM slot from the shared org token bucket.\n    Bucket refills at ORG_RPM_LIMIT tokens per minute using Redis.\n    Returns True if a slot was acquired, False if timeout.\n    \"\"\"\n    deadline = time.monotonic() + timeout_sec\n    bucket_key = \"proxy:org:rpm_bucket\"\n    refill_key  = \"proxy:org:last_refill\"\n\n    while time.monotonic() < deadline:\n        async with redis_client.pipeline() as pipe:\n            try:\n                now = time.time()\n                pipe.watch(bucket_key, refill_key)\n                last_refill = float(await redis_client.get(refill_key) or now)\n                tokens = int(await redis_client.get(bucket_key) or ORG_RPM_LIMIT)\n\n                # Refill: add tokens proportional to elapsed time\n                elapsed = now - last_refill\n                new_tokens = min(ORG_RPM_LIMIT, tokens + int(elapsed * ORG_RPM_LIMIT / 60))\n\n                pipe.multi()\n                if new_tokens > 0:\n                    pipe.set(bucket_key, new_tokens - 1)\n                    pipe.set(refill_key, now)\n                    await pipe.execute()\n                    return True\n                else:\n                    await pipe.reset()\n                    await asyncio.sleep(0.1)  # wait for refill\n            except redis.WatchError:\n                continue  # retry on concurrent modification\n\n    return False  # timeout\n\n\nasync def acquire_team_slot(team_id: str) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"\n    Enforce per-team soft cap using a sliding window counter in Redis.\n    \"\"\"\n    cap_fraction = TEAM_CAPS.get(team_id, 0.10)\n    team_limit   = int(ORG_RPM_LIMIT * cap_fraction)\n    window_key   = f\"proxy:team:{team_id}:rpm_window\"\n\n    # Sliding 60-second window using a sorted set\n    now_ms = int(time.time() * 1000)\n    cutoff = now_ms - 60_000\n\n    async with redis_client.pipeline() as pipe:\n        pipe.zremrangebyscore(window_key, 0, cutoff)\n        pipe.zcard(window_key)\n        _, count = await pipe.execute()\n\n    if count >= team_limit:\n        return False  # team cap exceeded \u2014 reject with 429\n\n    await redis_client.zadd(window_key, {str(now_ms): now_ms})\n    await redis_client.expire(window_key, 120)\n    return True\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Proxy Handler"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "ANTHROPIC_BASE = \"https://api.anthropic.com\"\n\n@app.api_route(\"/{path:path}\", methods=[\"GET\", \"POST\", \"DELETE\"])\nasync def proxy_request(\n    path: str,\n    request: Request,\n    x_api_key: str = Header(...),\n) -> StreamingResponse:\n    # Authenticate: map virtual key \u2192 team\n    team_id = TEAM_KEYS.get(x_api_key)\n    if not team_id:\n        raise HTTPException(status_code=401, detail=\"Unknown proxy key\")\n\n    # Enforce per-team soft cap\n    if not await acquire_team_slot(team_id):\n        raise HTTPException(\n            status_code=429,\n            detail=f\"Team {team_id} rate cap exceeded. Retry after 1s.\",\n            headers={\"Retry-After\": \"1\"},\n        )\n\n    # Enforce org-level pool\n    if not await acquire_org_slot(timeout_sec=10.0):\n        raise HTTPException(\n            status_code=429,\n            detail=\"Org rate limit pool exhausted. Retry after 1s.\",\n            headers={\"Retry-After\": \"1\"},\n        )\n\n    # Forward to Anthropic with real key\n    body  = await request.body()\n    headers = {\n        \"x-api-key\":         ANTHROPIC_API_KEY,\n        \"anthropic-version\": request.headers.get(\"anthropic-version\", \"2023-06-01\"),\n        \"content-type\":      \"application/json\",\n    }\n\n    async def stream_response():\n        async with httpx.AsyncClient(timeout=120) as client:\n            async with client.stream(\n                request.method,\n                f\"{ANTHROPIC_BASE}/{path}\",\n                headers=headers,\n                content=body,\n            ) as upstream:\n                async for chunk in upstream.aiter_bytes():\n                    yield chunk\n\n    return StreamingResponse(\n        stream_response(),\n        status_code=200,\n        media_type=\"text/event-stream\",\n    )\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Starting the Proxy"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "bash"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Install dependencies\npip install fastapi uvicorn httpx redis\n\n# Start Redis (required for distributed rate limiting)\ndocker run -d -p 6379:6379 redis:7-alpine\n\n# Run the proxy\nuvicorn proxy:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000 --workers 4\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Callers authenticate with their team's proxy key and use the standard Anthropic SDK format:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import anthropic\n\n# Team A's service \u2014 uses its virtual proxy key, points at the proxy\nclient = anthropic.Anthropic(\n    api_key=\"proxy-key-team-a\",\n    base_url=\"http://proxy.internal:8000\",\n)\n\nresponse = client.messages.create(\n    model=\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n    max_tokens=512,\n    messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Hello\"}],\n)\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Burst Borrowing: Using Idle Capacity"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Soft caps are "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "soft",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ": when the org-level pool has capacity and a team's own cap allows it, any team can burst above its nominal allocation. The design above already handles this \u2014 the per-team limit only rejects when that team's sliding window exceeds its cap, not when the pool is available to others."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "To implement true burst borrowing (a team can use another team's idle quota), track utilization per-team and release surplus to a shared burst pool:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "async def acquire_with_burst(team_id: str) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"\n    Try team's own cap first; if exceeded, try burst pool (idle slack from others).\n    \"\"\"\n    if await acquire_team_slot(team_id):\n        return True\n\n    # Try the burst pool: capacity not claimed by any team in last 5s\n    burst_key = \"proxy:burst:pool\"\n    burst = int(await redis_client.get(burst_key) or 0)\n    if burst > 0:\n        await redis_client.decr(burst_key)\n        return True\n\n    return False\n\n\nasync def refill_burst_pool():\n    \"\"\"\n    Periodically compute unused capacity and add to burst pool.\n    Run as a background task.\n    \"\"\"\n    while True:\n        total_used = 0\n        for team_id in TEAM_CAPS:\n            window_key = f\"proxy:team:{team_id}:rpm_window\"\n            cutoff = int((time.time() - 60) * 1000)\n            await redis_client.zremrangebyscore(window_key, 0, cutoff)\n            used = await redis_client.zcard(window_key)\n            total_used += used\n        idle = max(0, ORG_RPM_LIMIT - total_used - 50)  # keep 50 in reserve\n        await redis_client.set(\"proxy:burst:pool\", idle, ex=10)\n        await asyncio.sleep(5)\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Per-Team Usage Reporting"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Expose an admin endpoint to view current utilization per team. Useful for capacity planning and debugging:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "@app.get(\"/admin/quota\")\nasync def quota_status(x_admin_key: str = Header(...)):\n    if x_admin_key != \"your-admin-secret\":\n        raise HTTPException(status_code=403)\n\n    now_ms = int(time.time() * 1000)\n    cutoff  = now_ms - 60_000\n    report  = {}\n\n    for team_id, cap_fraction in TEAM_CAPS.items():\n        window_key = f\"proxy:team:{team_id}:rpm_window\"\n        await redis_client.zremrangebyscore(window_key, 0, cutoff)\n        used = await redis_client.zcard(window_key)\n        soft_limit = int(ORG_RPM_LIMIT * cap_fraction)\n        report[team_id] = {\n            \"used_rpm\":   used,\n            \"soft_cap\":   soft_limit,\n            \"utilization\": f\"{100*used/soft_limit:.1f}%\" if soft_limit else \"N/A\",\n        }\n\n    org_bucket = int(await redis_client.get(\"proxy:org:rpm_bucket\") or ORG_RPM_LIMIT)\n    report[\"_org\"] = {\"remaining_bucket\": org_bucket, \"limit\": ORG_RPM_LIMIT}\n    return report\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "TPM Pooling (Token-Per-Minute)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Anthropic limits both requests per minute (RPM) and tokens per minute (TPM). Pool TPM the same way, but count tokens from the response's usage field:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# After the Anthropic response is received, record token usage\nasync def record_token_usage(team_id: str, input_tokens: int, output_tokens: int):\n    total = input_tokens + output_tokens\n    tpm_key = f\"proxy:team:{team_id}:tpm_window\"\n    now_ms  = int(time.time() * 1000)\n    await redis_client.zadd(tpm_key, {f\"{now_ms}:{total}\": now_ms})\n    await redis_client.expire(tpm_key, 120)\n\n    # Also record against org-level TPM bucket\n    # (decrement org_tpm_bucket by `total` tokens)\n"
          }
        ]
      },
