        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Summary"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A custom proxy consolidates org-level Anthropic rate limits into a shared pool and enforces per-team soft caps using a sliding-window counter in Redis. Teams call the proxy with virtual keys; the proxy forwards with the real API key. Burst borrowing allows a quiet team's idle quota to be used by a busy team without explicit reallocation. Build a custom proxy when you need burst pooling, custom auth integration, or proprietary metering that off-the-shelf gateways (LiteLLM, Portkey) do not support. For simpler needs, prefer a managed gateway to avoid the operational overhead of running a custom proxy."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
